divs: Sighting Detailswhile looking for a house in Cape Coral, Fl I noticed an object that I thought was a blimp in the street view. It bothered me and after a while I looked at it more closely and found that if I moved one frame in google earth the object was shown moving along the roadside power lines and traveled from horizon to horizon in 4 frames which covered not more than 200 feet in front of the house I was looking at. One frame was close enough to see circular spots clearly on the object that could be like holes or lights or something - to me it almost looked like a giant whiffle ball but not really. the detail is very good.
Summary: on google earth - excellent visual of a 20' sphere going in opposite direction of google veichle at high speed following power lines daytime
